  <Summary>Snoid introduces himself to the audience and puts Mr. Crumb in his place.

Beverly suffers the wrath of Snoid's artistic rage.

All it takes is one Snoid and his hand to give birth.

One of the most famous of Crumb stories shows the evolution of a landscape from idyllic grassland to its cluttered commercial present.

Snoid meets up with a streetwalker to indulge in a particular fetish.</Summary>
